    return items.stream().anyMatch(s -&gt; !s.equals(&quot;apple&quot;));

or cute but a little less obvious:

    return items.stream().allMatch(&quot;apple&quot;::equals);

With **Stream IPA** you can achieve that by using terminal operation [`allMath()`](https://docs.oracle.com/en/java/javase/17/docs/api/java.base/java/util/stream/Stream.html#allMatch(java.util.function.Predicate)) that takes a *predicate* (*function represented by boolean condition*) and checks whether all elements in the stream match with the given *predicate*.

